The complete list of FHIR profiles, RESTful operations, and search parameters supported by CARIN Blue Button Servers are defined.</p></p><h3 id=\"behavior\">FHIR RESTful Capabilities</h3><p>The CARIN Blue Button Server <strong>SHALL</strong>:</p><ol><li>Support the CARIN Blue Button Patient resource profile.</li><li>Support at least one additional resource profile from the list of CARIN Blue Button Profiles.</li><li>Implement the RESTful behavior according to the FHIR specification.</li><li>Return the following response classes:\n<ul><li>(Status 400): invalid parameter</li><li>(Status 401/4xx): unauthorized request</li><li>(Status 403): insufficient scope</li><li>(Status 404): unknown resource</li><li>(Status 410): deleted resource.</li></ul>\n</li><li>Support json source formats for all CARIN Blue Button interactions.</li></ol><p>The CARIN Blue Button Server <strong>SHOULD</strong>:</p><ol><li>Support xml source formats for all CARIN Blue Button interactions.</li><li>Identify the CARIN Blue Button profiles supported as part of the FHIR <code>meta.profile</code> attribute for each instance.</li></ol><p id=\"security\"><strong>Security:</strong></p><ol><li>See the <a href=\"security.html\">General Security Considerations</a> section for requirements and recommendations.</li><li>A server <strong>SHALL</strong> reject any unauthorized requests by returning an <code>HTTP 401</code> unauthorized response code.</li></ol><hr/><br/></div>"
